01:11:02,160 --> 01:11:05,789
"I have fallen into terrible straits
and am about to be murdered."

957
01:11:05,880 --> 01:11:08,348
Which, of course, was not the case.

958
01:11:08,440 --> 01:11:13,833
This dog, the one without a master,
what sort of dog was he?.

959
01:11:13,920 --> 01:11:20,519
Oh, the best of fellows. Adventurous
and carefree, fearless and bold.

960
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:25,230
But you said he was whining
and snivelling about being murdered.

961
01:11:25,320 --> 01:11:27,595
Oh, that was just his complaint.

962
01:11:27,680 --> 01:11:29,750
How did you meet him,
this friend?.

963
01:11:31,520 --> 01:11:36,036
He would Ieave messages
on the cart that brought the milk.

964
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:01,391
And i would reply.

965
01:12:02,640 --> 01:12:05,598
And then one day, he came to our door.

966
01:12:06,400 --> 01:12:08,994
Well, I told him to go away
or I would chase him

967
01:12:09,080 --> 01:12:12,311
and I barked my most enormous bark
and made myself very huge.

968
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:15,830
But he wasn't afraid and said so.

969
01:12:16,840 --> 01:12:22,119
You weren't... how will I put it...
a female by any chance, were you?.

970
01:12:22,760 --> 01:12:24,512
- Of course he wasn't.
- Not at all.

971
01:12:24,600 --> 01:12:26,750
We were just good friends.

972
01:12:29,320 --> 01:12:33,916
He'd Ied a very interesting Iife
and knew many more things than I did,

973
01:12:34,000 --> 01:12:36,309
which he told me about
in considerable detail.

974
01:12:36,400 --> 01:12:39,836
- How did he tell you?.
- In the messages that he Ieft me.

975
01:12:41,040 --> 01:12:43,076
And I would Ieave word of my doings,

976
01:12:43,160 --> 01:12:45,469
which, I confess, were not comparable to his,

977
01:12:45,560 --> 01:12:48,916
because all I'd ever done was
go for evening walks with the Master.

978
01:12:49,000 --> 01:12:51,150
And while they were enjoyable outings,

979
01:12:52,600 --> 01:12:56,878
they were but moon-cast shadows
compared to his adventures.

980
01:12:56,960 --> 01:12:59,952
Did you ever go
on an adventure with him?.

981
01:13:00,040 --> 01:13:03,157
(Spanley) Indeed.
The greatest of my Iife.

982
01:13:04,240 --> 01:13:07,073
i remember the Master had to go away
and i couldn 't go with him.

983
01:13:07,160 --> 01:13:09,355
And i was going to follow him,

984
01:13:09,440 --> 01:13:14,150
but then my friend came
and he proposed we have an adventure.

985
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:24,590
Since the Master was leaving,
i said yes.

986
01:13:24,680 --> 01:13:26,591
And off we went.

987
01:13:36,280 --> 01:13:41,798
What a day that was to be a dog and
to be with one who knew how to be a dog.

988
01:13:41,880 --> 01:13:45,077
For I confess, happy though I was
to belong to the Master,

989
01:13:45,160 --> 01:13:51,395
until that day I had barely glimpsed
the glories of dogdom.

990
01:13:54,160 --> 01:13:57,994
He introduced me
to the joys of chasing animals.

991
01:13:58,080 --> 01:14:01,629
A matter in which
I was Iargely unversed,

992
01:14:01,720 --> 01:14:04,712
having previously only had the opportunity
to chase a couple of cats.

993
01:14:05,840 --> 01:14:07,796
Cats are of no use for chasing

994
01:14:07,880 --> 01:14:10,519
for, not knowing the rules,
they invariably climb up trees,

995
01:14:10,600 --> 01:14:13,114
a habit I find contemptible.

996
01:14:13,200 --> 01:14:17,159
Horses, on the other hand,
understand the rules perfectly

997
01:14:17,240 --> 01:14:19,754
and enter the business in good spirit.

1000
01:14:36,800 --> 01:14:39,917
But of all the creatures
that a dog can chase,

1001
01:14:40,000 --> 01:14:44,596
none exceed sheep for sheer pleasure.

1003
01:14:50,400 --> 01:14:55,428
Their fear drifts in clouds behind them
and you breathe it in as you run along,

1004
01:14:55,520 --> 01:14:58,159
so you become quite intoxicated by it.

1005
01:14:59,960 --> 01:15:04,795
it's as if one is not so much running
but flying on it.

1006
01:15:04,880 --> 01:15:09,112
Or perhaps swimming
might be more a exact description.

1007
01:15:10,280 --> 01:15:14,432
Were it not for their master appearing,
we might have chased them all day.

1008
01:15:17,640 --> 01:15:19,437
Be gone!

1009
01:15:19,520 --> 01:15:21,397
My friend didn't care,

1010
01:15:21,480 --> 01:15:24,995
but I thought we might be seized
and prevented from further adventures,

1011
01:15:25,080 --> 01:15:27,719
so I persuaded him to Ieave.

1012
01:15:27,800 --> 01:15:30,439
So we went into the woods.

1013
01:15:30,520 --> 01:15:35,150
And there we had the good fortune
to come across... a rabbit.

1014
01:15:40,080 --> 01:15:43,311
It's not commonly known
that rabbit scent,

1015
01:15:43,400 --> 01:15:46,995
particularly when it's frightened -
and this one was very frightened indeed -

1016
01:15:47,080 --> 01:15:49,230
does not Iie along the ground,

1017
01:15:49,320 --> 01:15:54,110
but rises in heaps
so you have to jump to inhale it.

1018
01:15:56,080 --> 01:16:00,073
When we'd had our fill of its fear,
we turned to catching it,

1019
01:16:00,160 --> 01:16:04,915
and in this endeavour my friend showed
what a splendid fellow he was,

1020
01:16:05,000 --> 01:16:07,833
for he drove
straight through the thicket,

1021
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:10,832
paying no heed
to its many inconveniences,

1022
01:16:10,920 --> 01:16:15,914
and sent the rabbit scuttling
to where I was stationed.

1024
01:16:40,240 --> 01:16:45,109
how much more satisfying
a recently alive rabbit tastes.

1025
01:16:45,200 --> 01:16:51,150
I'm afraid the masters fail
to appreciate fur, guts and bones

1026
01:16:51,240 --> 01:16:53,549
for the delicacies that they are.

1027
01:16:56,440 --> 01:16:59,477
Then it was time to quench our thirst.

1028
01:17:05,680 --> 01:17:10,435
And then, as in all things
that befell us on that glorious day,

1029
01:17:10,520 --> 01:17:14,433
we came across some water
that had gathered in a hollow.

1030
01:17:17,280 --> 01:17:19,396
Then, after we drank our fill,

1031
01:17:19,480 --> 01:17:23,632
we rolled in it
to give ourselves a good glow

1032
01:17:23,720 --> 01:17:28,271
and then we went into the woods
to rest in the shade.

1033
01:17:31,480 --> 01:17:33,596
- Perhaps we should take our...
- Father.

1034
01:17:33,680 --> 01:17:35,910
Be quiet and sit down, please.

1035
01:17:42,240 --> 01:17:45,915
You went into the woods and...

1036
01:17:47,640 --> 01:17:49,631
And we slept.

1037
01:17:49,720 --> 01:17:53,076
That most sublime of states,

1038
01:17:53,160 --> 01:17:57,278
when a dream dreams you
rather than the other way round.

1039
01:18:17,720 --> 01:18:21,554
And when we awoke, the moon was rising.

1040
01:18:21,640 --> 01:18:26,077
it was just on the other side of the woods,
so we set about surprising it.

1041
01:18:36,880 --> 01:18:40,555
And we came very close to catching it,
for it was slow to get up.

1042
01:18:41,640 --> 01:18:43,915
But just when we were almost on it,

1043
01:18:44,000 --> 01:18:47,675
my friend couldn't control himself
any Ionger and Iet out a cry.

1044
01:18:54,440 --> 01:18:56,795
And had we been there
but a moment sooner,

1045
01:18:56,880 --> 01:18:59,872
we surely would have seized it
and torn it apart Iike the rabbit.

1046
01:18:59,960 --> 01:19:04,317
How it would have tasted, I cannot tell.

1047
01:19:04,400 --> 01:19:09,872
So we told it what a great
cowardly, unsmelling thing it was

1048
01:19:09,960 --> 01:19:14,636
and if we ever caught up with it,
it would surely regret it.

1049
01:19:19,560 --> 01:19:23,075
Then we turned around and went home.

1050
01:19:24,600 --> 01:19:26,670
So you knew the way home?.

1051
01:19:26,760 --> 01:19:30,753
Oh, yes. Turn towards home and go there.

1052
01:19:32,800 --> 01:19:37,112
But you had been out all day, running free.
How far from home were you?.

1053
01:19:37,200 --> 01:19:43,036
Yes, we'd gone many overs, that is true.
How many, I couldn't tell.

1054
01:19:43,120 --> 01:19:44,917
Overs?.

1055
01:19:45,000 --> 01:19:50,438
Overs. Many overs. Over woods and
fields, streams and hills. Many overs.

1056
01:19:53,040 --> 01:19:57,113
And you just... turned towards home?.

1057
01:19:58,600 --> 01:20:01,990
- How else would one do it?.
- Then why...

1058
01:20:02,080 --> 01:20:05,709
And I knew that I should be beaten

1059
01:20:05,800 --> 01:20:09,588
and I remembered my friend's complaint
that I would use

1060
01:20:09,680 --> 01:20:12,911
and how delicious it would feel

1061
01:20:13,000 --> 01:20:17,232
when the beating had stopped
and the insults had finished.

1062
01:20:19,400 --> 01:20:23,075
Yes, the glow of having paid the price
for wrongdoing.

1063
01:20:26,120 --> 01:20:28,111
And were you punished?.

1064
01:20:29,440 --> 01:20:31,635
No, not on that occasion.

1065
01:20:32,920 --> 01:20:35,673
Why was that?. Do you know?.

1066
01:20:38,160 --> 01:20:42,472
Because a very remarkable thing
happened on the way back...

1067
01:20:54,560 --> 01:20:57,518
which I cannot fully explain.

1068
01:20:57,600 --> 01:21:02,071
One moment we were running along
side by side, heading for home, and the next...

1069
01:21:26,960 --> 01:21:29,520
we were not.

1070
01:21:35,160 --> 01:21:37,720
I cannot say what happened.

1071
01:21:38,560 --> 01:21:41,279
Perhaps it was a dream
and I wakened from it.

1073
01:22:07,440 --> 01:22:09,431
Was there any pain?.

1074
01:22:11,560 --> 01:22:15,473
Pain?. No, I cannot say there was.

1075
01:22:22,960 --> 01:22:25,394
All i can remember
is how clear the night was,

1076
01:22:25,480 --> 01:22:27,471
with the moon-cast shadows

1077
01:22:28,440 --> 01:22:32,194
and the earth rising underneath me,

1078
01:22:32,280 --> 01:22:35,158
and home in my heart
and the Master waiting.

1079
01:22:37,360 --> 01:22:40,079
But no, no pain.

1080
01:23:15,120 --> 01:23:19,113
I am most glad to hear it.

1081
01:23:24,800 --> 01:23:27,712
If you will excuse me.

1082
01:23:30,120 --> 01:23:32,156
Did I say something to upset you, sir?.

1083
01:23:32,240 --> 01:23:35,277
No, no, no, not at all.

1084
01:23:38,320 --> 01:23:41,676
I am put in memory of my son Harrington.

1085
01:23:43,480 --> 01:23:45,516
That is all.

1086
01:23:58,880 --> 01:24:00,438
Erm...

1087
01:24:03,320 --> 01:24:06,596
Harrington was, erm...
killed in the Boer War...

1088
01:24:08,920 --> 01:24:11,070
returning from a patrol.

1089
01:24:11,160 --> 01:24:13,116
That's all we know.

1090
01:24:15,600 --> 01:24:18,353
The, erm... body was never recovered.

1091
01:24:50,520 --> 01:24:52,317
Are you all right, Mr Fisk?.

1092
01:24:58,480 --> 01:25:00,755
He was shot.

1093
01:25:03,480 --> 01:25:05,596
Yes.

1095
01:25:11,720 --> 01:25:15,235
Oh. There, there.

1096
01:25:21,200 --> 01:25:23,395
Better Iate than never, Mr Fisk.

1097
01:25:27,440 --> 01:25:29,237
Come with me.

1098
01:25:33,640 --> 01:25:35,756
In you go, Mr Fisk.

1099
01:25:41,080 --> 01:25:43,071
Sit yourself down.

1100
01:25:49,520 --> 01:25:52,318
He does mither on, that dean of yours.

1101
01:26:10,520 --> 01:26:13,080
I do hope whatever I said
did not upset him.

1102
01:26:13,160 --> 01:26:18,234
Excuse me. I was talking
to Mrs Brimley about the old days.

1103
01:26:18,320 --> 01:26:21,790
Thank you, Dean, for coming.
It was a memorable evening.

1104
01:26:21,880 --> 01:26:23,598
No, thank you, sir.

1105
01:26:23,680 --> 01:26:27,070
I fear the Tokay
rendered me somewhat unsociable.

1106
01:26:27,160 --> 01:26:30,709
It has a tendency
to make me withdraw into myself.

1107
01:26:30,800 --> 01:26:35,430
Not at all. You were all
that could be hoped for in a guest.

1108
01:26:35,520 --> 01:26:38,034
You know your way home from here?.

1109
01:26:38,120 --> 01:26:42,398
Just turn towards it
is the best way, I'm told.

1110
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:46,837
I'm going in the dean's direction.
I'II see that he gets there this time.

1111
01:26:46,920 --> 01:26:49,957
- Good of you to come, Mr Wrather.
- Wouldn't have missed it for the world.

1112
01:26:50,040 --> 01:26:52,110
- Good night, sir.
- Good night.

1113
01:27:04,160 --> 01:27:06,196
You know, Mr Wrather,

1114
01:27:06,280 --> 01:27:10,751
I have the most persistent notion
that we have met before.

1115
01:27:13,400 --> 01:27:16,551
One often feels that about colonials,
Dean.

1116
01:27:16,640 --> 01:27:20,599
Yes, I have heard that said.
Nevertheless...

1117
01:27:20,680 --> 01:27:25,913
You're not in the market for a new rug,
are you?. I've this good friend in Marrakesh.

1118
01:27:26,000 --> 01:27:27,911
Marrakesh?.

1119
01:27:28,000 --> 01:27:30,594
Colourful, exciting place,
if you know the right people.

1120
01:27:30,680 --> 01:27:34,958
- I know the right people.
- Something of an adventure, I imagine.

1121
01:27:41,040 --> 01:27:44,350
He can put away the Tokay,
I'II say that for the dean.

1122
01:27:44,440 --> 01:27:47,716
I thought for a moment
we might have had to open the third bottle.

1123
01:27:47,800 --> 01:27:49,916
Oh, two was ample, I think.

1124
01:27:50,000 --> 01:27:52,958
He goes on a bit
when he's in his cups, though.

1125
01:27:55,080 --> 01:27:57,071
Thank you, Father.

1126
01:28:01,240 --> 01:28:05,074
One moment you are running along,
the next you are no more.

1127
01:28:08,640 --> 01:28:11,029
Well...

1128
01:28:30,520 --> 01:28:34,638
- I will see you next Thursday.
- Or any day that suits.

1129
01:28:34,720 --> 01:28:37,678
Mustn't get too set in our ways.

1130
01:28:39,400 --> 01:28:41,391
Good night, Henslowe.

1131
01:28:43,600 --> 01:28:45,591
Good night, Father.

1132
01:28:56,760 --> 01:28:58,876
God knows
what they were on about.

1133
01:28:58,960 --> 01:29:02,748
Something about rabbits tasting better
with their fur on.

1134
01:29:02,840 --> 01:29:05,752
You won't catch me cooking them,
that's all I can tell you.

1136
01:29:10,520 --> 01:29:13,637
Then, he comes in here.

1137
01:29:15,400 --> 01:29:17,630
First time in God knows how Iong.

1138
01:29:19,240 --> 01:29:23,552
And he stands...
Iooking at that photograph,

1139
01:29:25,080 --> 01:29:27,071
sobbing his heart out.

1140
01:29:44,960 --> 01:29:46,916
Morning, Mrs Brimley.

1141
01:29:47,000 --> 01:29:49,673
- It's not Thursday, you know.
- No, I know.

1142
01:29:51,960 --> 01:29:56,158
- How's Father?.
- Well, I don't know, really.

1143
01:29:56,240 --> 01:29:58,470
Here, boy!

1144
01:29:58,560 --> 01:30:00,790
Wasn't my idea, you know.

1145
01:30:00,880 --> 01:30:03,189
The day after that dinner,

1146
01:30:03,280 --> 01:30:07,034
he sent me round to see
that friend of yours, the one who was here.

1147
01:30:07,880 --> 01:30:10,838
- Mr Wrather?.
- Sent me round with a Ietter, he did.

1148
01:30:10,920 --> 01:30:13,957
Next day he shows up with a dog.

1149
01:30:16,200 --> 01:30:20,239
- What kind of dog?.
- Oh, one of those, erm...

1150
01:30:20,320 --> 01:30:22,629
- Oh, Iike before.
- A spaniel?.

1151
01:30:22,720 --> 01:30:24,711
Must be one of the seven.

1152
01:30:24,800 --> 01:30:26,438
CIever boy!

1153
01:30:26,520 --> 01:30:29,398
One's quite enough
in this house, thank you very much.

1154
01:30:29,480 --> 01:30:32,517
It's already chewed a cushion.

1155
01:30:32,600 --> 01:30:34,830
He's in the garden.

1156
01:30:36,080 --> 01:30:42,269
Imagine, Mr Fisk in the garden.
He'II be growing roses next.

1157
01:30:49,440 --> 01:30:51,192
Twist!

1159
01:31:13,600 --> 01:31:16,353
That was the end of my talks
with Dean Spanley,

1160
01:31:17,960 --> 01:31:20,235
although my father
sometimes saw him at the club.

1161
01:31:22,080 --> 01:31:24,992
Don 't know what they talked about,
if anything.

1162
01:31:26,280 --> 01:31:31,400
As for the question of reincarnation,
i resolved to wait and see,

1163
01:31:31,480 --> 01:31:35,439
albeit with more anticipation
than hitherto.

1164
01:31:36,760 --> 01:31:39,797
And should i find myself
in the form of a dog,

1165
01:31:39,880 --> 01:31:41,871
i trust i will be so fortunate

1166
01:31:41,960 --> 01:31:47,239
as to belong to a master
as kind as my father.


